<task id="R4-099" project="smart-todo-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>W-1 — Widget chrome consolidation + Pattern D alignment</title>
    <phase>Phase 2: Wave D (post-PR-384 widget parity)</phase>
    <workstream>W</workstream>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>0.5-1 day</estimated-effort>
    <tags>widget, smart-todo, pattern-d, fluent-v9, dataverse, spaarkeai, legalworkspace</tags>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>R4-020 (widget exists), R4-030 (Code Page Header search reference)</dependencies>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/todo.registration.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components/src/widgets/SmartTodoWidget/SmartTodoWidget.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components/src/widgets/SmartTodoWidget/SmartTodoWidget.styles.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/calendar.registration.ts (canonical reference)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/components/Header/Header.tsx (search-input reference)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
Close UAT issues 2 + 3 + 5 from the 2026-06-18 widget-parity audit by collapsing the LegalWorkspace SmartTodo shim to Calendar's canonical Pattern D shape (no section title, no section toolbar) and rebuilding the widget's PaneHeader as the sole chrome — title "Smart To Do", single toolbar with `[SearchBox, +, Open, refresh]`. Result: one title, one toolbar, search lives in the toolbar.
  </prompt>

  <role>
React + Fluent v9 widget engineer with deep familiarity with the Pattern D dual-use widget pattern (Calendar canonical) and the LegalWorkspace section registry contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
The SmartTodo workspace widget renders ONE title bar ("Smart To Do") and ONE toolbar containing `[SearchBox, +, Open, refresh]`. The LegalWorkspace shim becomes structural-only (no section title, no section toolbar) — mirrors `calendar.registration.ts` shape exactly. Search filters the rendered list locally (no OData round-trip needed for v1). Open button is selection-aware (disabled until a card is selected). The widget continues to mount cleanly in BOTH system-loaded and user-added workspace contexts.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="audit-findings">projects/smart-todo-r4/notes/d-widget-parity-audit-2026-06-18.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/smart-todo-r4/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="architecture">docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-DASHBOARD-AND-WIDGET-MODEL.md</file>
    <file purpose="canonical-pattern-d">src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/calendar.registration.ts</file>
    <file purpose="search-reference">src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/components/Header/Header.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="pattern">.claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-component-authoring.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 + Griffel `makeStyles` + semantic tokens mandatory; no inline styles, no v8 components</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Widget stays in `@spaarke/smart-todo-components` peer package — no inline component definitions in solution-specific source</constraint>
    <constraint source="Pattern D (Calendar)">LegalWorkspace shim is structural-only: declares the section but contributes ZERO chrome (no title, no toolbar). All user-facing chrome lives in the widget itself.</constraint>
    <constraint source="audit issue 5">Exactly ONE title rendered ("Smart To Do"); exactly ONE toolbar `[SearchBox, +, Open, refresh]`</constraint>
    <constraint source="audit issue 3">SearchBox lives INSIDE the widget's PaneHeader toolbar, not as a separate section</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-09">Rebuild + redeploy from master after R4-100 and R4-101 also land; this task is one of three; do NOT deploy from branch</constraint>
    <constraint source="durable user instruction">spaarkedev1 deploys are master-only; do NOT propose a branch deploy</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>workspace/widget Pattern D</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-DASHBOARD-AND-WIDGET-MODEL.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-COMPONENTIZATION-AUDIT.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/BUILD-A-NEW-WORKSPACE-WIDGET.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-v9-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-component-library.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-component-authoring.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Calendar Pattern D shim shape" location="src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/calendar.registration.ts">
        Canonical Pattern D — the shim declares the section but contributes ZERO chrome. The widget owns 100% of user-facing chrome. SmartTodo's shim must collapse to this shape.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="SearchBox in PaneHeader" location="src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/components/Header/Header.tsx:268-273">
        Reference for SearchBox styling + debounce. The widget's toolbar version is a more compact variant of the same component.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      UAT screenshot 2026-06-18 showed two title bars + two toolbar rows in the widget — root cause: the LW shim declares a section title + section toolbar that DUPLICATE the widget's own PaneHeader chrome. This violates the Calendar canonical Pattern D where the shim is structural-only. Search was also entirely missing from the widget (Code Page has it; widget has none).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="R4-020" status="must-complete">Widget exists in @spaarke/smart-todo-components peer package</dependency>
      <dependency task="R4-030" status="must-complete">Code Page Header search pattern (Header.tsx Row 2) is the reference</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>R4-100 (W-2) lands after this — it touches `todo.registration.ts` for the open-to-form callback rewrite + refetch wiring. Serialize on the same file.</item>
      <item>R4-101 (W-3) is parallel-safe with this task — different files (peer package hooks + widget item rendering).</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check">Confirm context &lt; 70%. Read the audit-findings note.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Read Calendar shim">Read `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/calendar.registration.ts` line by line to confirm its shape: no section title, no section toolbar.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Read SmartTodo shim current state">Read `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/todo.registration.ts` — confirm the duplicate-chrome layers at lines ~188-222 (section toolbar) and ~232 (section title).</step>
    <step order="3" name="Strip shim chrome">Remove `title: "My To Do List"` from the section config. Remove the entire section-toolbar block. Confirm shim becomes structural-only and mirrors Calendar's shape.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Widget title rename">Change widget default title prop from "My To Do List" to "Smart To Do". Update the prop's default in `SmartTodoWidget.tsx`.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Widget toolbar consolidation">Refactor `SmartTodoWidget.tsx` PaneHeader right slot into a single toolbar: `[SearchBox, +, Open, refresh]`. Use Fluent v9 `<Toolbar>` landmark. Open button must be selection-aware (disabled when no card selected) — mirror the Code Page's `SelectionAwareToolbar` pattern from `@spaarke/ui-components`. The `+` invokes `onAddTodo` (existing callback). Refresh invokes `refetch` (existing pattern). Open invokes `onOpenTodo` (existing callback — R4-100 will rewrite its target).</step>
    <step order="6" name="SearchBox wiring">Add `searchQuery` state to widget (local `useState`); SearchBox value-binds to it with a short debounce (~150ms). Filter the rendered items in-memory by case-insensitive substring match against `sprk_subject` (and optionally `sprk_description` if cheap to include). Do NOT rebuild the OData query for search; local filter is sufficient for the small result set the widget shows.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Selection state">Add a single-select model (or 0..1) for the widget cards so Open's selection-awareness has a real source of truth. Card click toggles selection; Open opens the selected card. (Multi-select is a Code Page feature; widget can stay single-select for simplicity.)</step>
    <step order="8" name="Styles">Update `SmartTodoWidget.styles.ts` with the new toolbar grid (SearchBox left-aligned, buttons right-aligned via Fluent v9 spacing tokens).</step>
    <step order="9" name="Build">`npm run build` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components` (tsc) + `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace` (Vite production).</step>
    <step order="10" name="Quality gates">Run `code-review` + `adr-check` on the modified files per task-execute Step 9.5. ADR-021 + ADR-012 are the binding ones.</step>
    <step order="11" name="Update task status">Flip POML status to `complete`. Update TASK-INDEX.md row + header counts. Document parity progress in commit message.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build (tsc on peer package; Vite on LegalWorkspace)</tool>
    <tool name="git">Stage + commit (main session pushes)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">Modified: src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/todo.registration.ts (chrome stripped)</output>
    <output type="code">Modified: src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components/src/widgets/SmartTodoWidget/SmartTodoWidget.tsx (title + toolbar + search + selection)</output>
    <output type="code">Modified: src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components/src/widgets/SmartTodoWidget/SmartTodoWidget.styles.ts (toolbar grid)</output>
    <output type="docs">Commit message references audit issues 2 + 3 + 5</output>
  </outputs>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="One title, one toolbar (issue 5)">
      <url>npm run dev or post-deploy spaarkedev1 SpaarkeAi workspace</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Mount the SmartTodo widget in the workspace</step>
        <step>Visually inspect the chrome — count the title bars (must be exactly 1) and toolbar rows (must be exactly 1)</step>
        <step>Confirm the title reads "Smart To Do"</step>
        <step>Confirm the toolbar contains `[SearchBox, +, Open, refresh]` in that order</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Exactly one title bar showing "Smart To Do"; exactly one toolbar with the 4 controls</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Search filters in-place (issue 3)">
      <steps>
        <step>Type a substring of an existing To Do's subject into the SearchBox</step>
        <step>Verify the rendered list filters to matching items only</step>
        <step>Clear the search; verify the full list returns</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>SearchBox filters items locally; debounced; no OData round-trip</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Open selection-awareness">
      <steps>
        <step>With no card selected, hover Open — verify it is disabled</step>
        <step>Click a card to select it; verify Open enables</step>
        <step>Click Open — verify it triggers the callback (target behavior is R4-100's scope)</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Open disabled when nothing selected; enabled + callback fires when selected</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="A11y (issue 2 / NFR-07)">
      <steps>
        <step>Tab through all chrome — verify focus visits SearchBox, +, Open, refresh in order</step>
        <step>Verify ARIA labels match Calendar widget convention</step>
        <step>Verify Toolbar landmark is present in the accessibility tree</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Keyboard accessible per WCAG 2.1 AA; matches Calendar widget</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">LegalWorkspace shim mirrors Calendar's shape — zero section title, zero section toolbar</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Widget renders exactly ONE title bar ("Smart To Do") and ONE toolbar `[SearchBox, +, Open, refresh]`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SearchBox filters items in-place with debounce; clearing it restores full list</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Open button is selection-aware (disabled when 0 selected; enabled when 1+ selected)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No Fluent v8 components introduced; no inline styles; Griffel + tokens used throughout</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` passes for both @spaarke/smart-todo-components and LegalWorkspace</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">A11y: Toolbar landmark present; tab order matches visual order; ARIA labels match Calendar widget convention</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">POML status flipped to complete; TASK-INDEX.md row + header counts updated</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
